
[1]extravagantly

   EXTRAV'AGANTLY, adv. In an extravagant manner; wildly; not within the
   limits of truth or probability. Men often write and talk extravagantly.

   1. Unreasonably; excessively. It is prudent not to praise or censure
   extravagantly.

   2. In a manner to use property without necessity or propriety, or to no
   good purpose; expensively, or profusely to an unjustifiable degree; as,
   to live, eat, drink, or dress extravagantly.
